    • Method Detail

      • getCode

        public java.lang.String getCode()
        A string depicting the state of the response.
        • "Ok" - Normal case
        • "NoMatch" - The input did not produce any matches. Feature will be an empty array.
        • "TooManyCoordinates" - There are more than 100 points in the request.
        • "InvalidInput" - message will hold an explanation of the invalid input.
        • "ProfileNotFound" - Profile should be mapbox.driving, mapbox.walking, or mapbox.cycling.
        Returns:
        String containing the code.
        Since:
        1.2.0

      • getMatchedPoints

        public Position[] getMatchedPoints(int submatch)
        Convenience method to obtain the list of matched points for other matches. When the matching algorithm cannot decide the correct match between two points, it will omit that line and create several sub-matches, each as a feature. The higher the number of features, the more likely that the input traces are poorly aligned to the road network.
        Parameters:
        submatch - Which sub-match you want to get the position for.
        Returns:
        Array of Position that have been map matched.
        Since:
        1.2.0
